title: Alabama Firm Recalls Corn Dog Products Due to Misbranding and Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, Sept. 28, 2012 - Foster Farms, a Demopolis, Ala. , establishment is recalling approximately 16,576 pounds of corn dog products because of misbranding and an allergen, milk, that is not declared on the label. The products subject to recall include: 2.67-lb. pound, 16-count packages...

establishment.name: Foster Poultry Farms
establishment.address:
232 Buddy Griffith Drive, North 
  Demopolis, AL 36732

impacted_products: 2.67-lb. pound, 16-count packages of "Foster Farms Honey Crunchy Corn Dogs."
